The paper deals with matching markets, which are a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT) and economics (cs.EC). The analysis involves quantifying signal to noise tradeoffs, which is a common theme in signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also use a simple utility model, which involves optimization and decision-making, making it relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
